In this statement, President Obama expresses his gratitude for the work of Caroline Atkinson, his Deputy National Security Advisor for International Economics, and announces her departure from his national security team. He highlights her role in coordinating responses to international financial crises, implementing economic sanctions, engaging with China, and achieving climate agreements. The President then introduces Adewale "Wally" Adeyemo as Caroline's successor, praising his previous work at the Treasury Department and his involvement in coordinating responses to the global recession and establishing the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau. President Obama expresses his confidence in Adeyemo's abilities and states that he will rely on his intellect, judgment, and dedication to sustain America's global economic leadership and create jobs and opportunities for the American people.